  "text": "The pathways for synthesis of 5-ALA use either succinyl-CoA and glycine (C-4 pathway), or glutamate (C-5 pathway). [CITATION_1] R. sphaeroides synthesizes 5-ALA through the C-4 pathway upon condensation of glycine and succinyl CoA by ALA synthetase (ALAS; succinyl-CoA:glycine C-succinyltransferase (decarboxylating); [EC: 2.3.1.37]). On the other hand, it also has the first enzyme (glutamyl-tRNA synthetase, RSP_0797, NCBI-GeneID: 3718415, [EC:6.1.1.17]) and the third enzyme (glutamate-1-semialdehyde aminotransferase, RSP_1569, NCBIGeneID: 3718596, [EC:5.4.3.8]) of the C-5 pathway. However, interestingly, the second enzyme, glutamyltRNA reductase, is absent in this bacterium. In the present study, the gene coding for glutamyl-tRNA reductase (the second enzyme) was cloned from Rhodospirillum rubrum (Rsp. Rubrum, DSM 467, ATCC 11170) and expressed in R. sphaeroides O.U.001. In this way, in addition to the C-4 pathway, the C-5 pathway was enabled to function upon assembling all the necessary genes.",
